JOHANNESBURG - The ANC Youth League is taking aim at Absa for its alleged role in apartheid-era looting.They're calling on members to hold demonstrations outside branches countrywide on Thursday.The Youth League is demanding that Absa pay back more than R2-billion to the state.OPINION: ABSA, SABC and the documentary that never airedTheir claims stem from a leaked version of the Public Protector's preliminary report on alleged apartheid-era looting.The investigation centred on claims the Mbeki administration had improperly failed to recover billions of rands in interest from an apartheid-era bailout given to Bankcorp.That's before it became Absa bank.Absa claims the report contains several factual and legal inaccuracies and plans to challenge its findings.eNCA